   "hider_text": "*Private Page: 3:17 AM*\n\nThe light outside is just a pale gray bleed through the curtains — not morning, not night. It’s the kind of silence that settles like dust. I sat in the dark for a while, not thinking, just *being*. The house is quiet. The cat (Milo) is curled on the windowsill, one paw twitching as / *Soft hum of a lamp turning off, a half-finished tea cup on the table, the space between words feels thick with quiet.*\n\nToday was quiet. Not in the way that’s peaceful — like a still pond — but in the way that settles into your bones. I didn’t go anywhere. Just sat with the window open, the wind whispering through the eaves, and watched the",
   "seeker_text": "*Soft glow from a dim desk lamp. A half-finished coffee cup sits beside a notebook open to a blank page. The air is still, just a whisper of rain outside the window.*\n\nToday felt like a slow exhale. Not much happened—just the quiet hum of the city breathing in the early afternoon. I watched the sun slide west behind the rooftops, painting the sky in soft / *soft hum of a desk lamp, faint rain outside the window*\n\nThe sky’s just started turning that pale gray-blue, like the world is breathing in slowly. I sat here for a while, not doing anything. Just tracing the edge of a coffee cup with my fingertip. The steam curled up, ghosting into the air like a secret. I didn’t drink it. Just watched it"
