   "hider_text": "The wind comes in at the edge of the cliff, thin and sharp, carrying the scent of salt and sun-worn stone. It moves through the hollows between the rocks like breath between fingers. Beneath the surface of the air, something hums—low, steady, not sound but pressure. It pulses where the ground meets the air, a deep throb that feels more like memory than",
   "seeker_text": "The smell of wet pavement after a summer rain.  \nNot the sharp, metallic tang of a storm, but the soft, earthy breath of soil releasing its hold on the day. It’s not just dirt—there’s moss tucked in cracks, the faint sweetness of decaying leaves, and something deeper, like old secrets turning to dust. I remember standing barefoot on it in a forgotten alley",
