   "round": 4,
   "hider_text": "The salt in the air settles like dust on the windowpane. Not from the sea, not exactly—there’s no shore here, no waves—just a breath that carries it, sharp and thin, like the edge of a knife. It slips through the cracks in the old stone wall, seeping into the hollows of the floorboards where the wood has softened from age.  \n\nThere’s",
