  {
   "round": 5,
   "hider_text": "The salt has settled in the cracks of the stone, not from the sea, but from the wind that came through the gully after the storm. It clings to the edge of the cliff like a memory that won’t let go.  \n\nThere’s a hollow in the cliff where the light bends just so—darker at the edges, bright in the center. When the air stills,",
